This paper is likely to belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category as it discusses the use of N-gram language models in humor detection. It may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories as these fields are closely related to natural language processing and humor detection. Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Computation and Language (cs.CC) are also possible sub-categories as they deal with language processing and analysis.
